iii 4123-2149-0255.7 AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS AMENDED AND RESTATED SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this Agreement) is entered into as of August 9, 2024 (the Effective Date), by and among Atrisco Solar SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (SF 1), Atrisco BESS SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (SF 2), Quail Ranch Solar SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (SF 3), Quail Ranch BESS SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (SF 4), and each New Co-Tenant from time to time party hereto (and together with SF 1, SF 2, SF 3, and SF 4, the Co-Tenants and each separately as a Co-Tenant) and SF 2 in its capacity as the Manager on the Effective Date (the Initial Manager, and collectively with the Co-Tenants, the Parties, and each individually a Party).
RECITALS:
A. The Parties are party to that certain Shared Facilities Agreement (the Existing SFA), dated November 17, 2023, and are entering into this Agreement to amend, restate and supersede the Existing SFA in all respects.
B. Atrisco Solar LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Atrisco PVCo) is developing an approximately 313.6 MWac/364.1 MWdc rated solar photovoltaic electricity generation and transmission facility on real property located in Bernalillo County, New Mexico that will include photovoltaic modules, inverters and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (collectively, the Atrisco PV Project).
C. Atrisco Energy Storage LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Atrisco BatteryCo) is developing an approximately 300 Mwac/1200 MWh battery energy storage facility on real property adjacent to the Atrisco PV Project also located in Bernalillo County, New Mexico that will include battery storage facilities and associated collection and interconnection lines, related facilities and improvements (collectively, the Atrisco BESS Project).
D. Quail Ranch Solar LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Quail Ranch PVCo) is developing an approximately 100 Mwac/130 MWdc rated solar photovoltaic electricity generation and transmission facility on real property located in Bernalillo County, New Mexico that will include photovoltaic modules, inverters and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (collectively, the Quail Ranch PV Project).
E. Quail Ranch Energy Storage LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Quail Ranch BatteryCo) is developing an approximately 100 MWac/400 MWh battery energy storage facility on real property adjacent to the Quail Ranch PV Project also located in Bernalillo County, New Mexico that will include battery storage facilities and associated collection and interconnection lines, related facilities, and improvements (collectively, the Quail Ranch BESS Project)
F. One or more new project companies (including, without limitation, those set forth on Exhibit G) may from time to time develop, construct, own, and operate other projects adjacent to or in the vicinity of the aforementioned projects and may desire to utilize the Shared Assets for the delivery of electricity subject to the conditions set forth herein (such new project companies and together with Atrisco PVCo, Atrisco BatteryCo, Quail Ranch PVCo, and Quail Ranch
4123-2149-0255.7BatteryCo are each hereinafter referred to as a Project Company, and the project and project site corresponding to each Project Company, each a Project and a Project Site, respectively). Each Project Company holds or shall hold its own individual real property rights (by option, lease, easement, right of way, in fee, or otherwise) to its respective Project Site.
G. The ownership, development, construction, operation, and maintenance of the Projects require the use of (i) certain real property more particularly described on Exhibit A-2 attached hereto (as amended or supplemented from time to time, the Shared Premises) and (ii) certain common infrastructure facilities supporting the construction, operation, and maintenance of the Projects, including electrical transmission facilities, a substation, operations and maintenance facilities, laydown and staging areas for construction, and other related facilities all as more particularly described in Exhibit C (collectively, the Shared BatteryCo Facilities).
H. Atrisco BatteryCo directly owns 100% ownership interest in and to each Co-Tenant. Each of the Co-Tenants (i) holds real property rights to the Shared Premises as a tenant in common and (ii) immediately prior to the Effective Date, owned an undivided interest in and to the Shared BatteryCo Facilities.
I. Each Co-Tenant acknowledges that Atrisco BatteryCo has obtained financing for the construction of the Shared BatteryCo Facilities from the City of Rio Rancho, New Mexico, through a transaction involving the issuance of industrial revenue bonds (the Industrial Revenue Bonds), all as contemplated by and pursuant to that certain Indenture, dated August 9, 2024, between the City of Rio Rancho, New Mexico (the City), Atrisco BatteryCo, Atrisco Energy Storage Bond Holder LLC, and BOKF, NA (such financing herein, the IRB Financing). In connection with the IRB Financing, on the Effective Date (i) each Co-Tenant transferred its interest in the Shared BatteryCo Facilities to Atrisco BatteryCo pursuant to that certain Bill of Sale (Co-Tenants), dated concurrently herewith, by and among Atriscto BatteryCo and the Co-Tenants (the Co-Tenants Bill of Sale) and (ii) Atrisco BatteryCo transferred its interest in the Shared BatteryCo Facilities to the City, in each case subject to the Co-Tenants right to repurchase the Shared BatteryCo Facilities at the expiration or earlier termination of the IRB Financing (the Right to Repurchase). The Right to Repurchase is described in that certain Lease Agreement, dated August 9, 2024, between the City and Atrisco BatteryCo entered into in connection with the IRB Financing (the IRB Lease).
J. Atrisco BatteryCo and each Co-Tenant are parties to that certain Shared Facilities Sublease Agreement, dated August 9, 2024 (the Shared Facilities Sublease), pursuant to which Atrisco BatteryCo has leased to each Co-Tenant the right to use and operate the Shared BatteryCo Facilities.
K. Each of SF 1 and SF 2 is simultaneously entering into an Amended and Restated Lease Agreement substantially in the form of Exhibit I with each of Atrisco PVCo and Atrisco BatteryCo, respectively, to provide the use of the Shared Facilities and the Shard Premises for the development, construction, operation and maintenance of the Applicable Project owned by such Project Company. Each of SF 3 and SF 4 will enter into a Lease Agreement substantially in the form of Exhibit I with each of Quail Ranch PVCo and Quail Ranch BatteryCo, respectively, to provide the use of the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises for the development, construction, operation and maintenance of the Applicable Project owned by such Project Company. Each of
2 4123-2149-0255.7the Amended and Restated Lease Agreements and the Lease Agreements shall be referred to herein as a Lease Agreement.
L. Atrisco PVCo, Atrisco BatteryCo, Quail Ranch PVCo, and Quail Ranch BatteryCo entered into (i) that certain Amended and Restated Standard Large Generator Interconnection Agreement (the Interconnection Agreement), dated as of October 19, 2023, with Public Service Company of New Mexico, a corporation organized and existing under the laws of the State of New Mexico (Transmission Provider or Transmission Owner), for the purpose of securing interconnection rights for the Applicable Projects and (ii) that certain Large Generator Interconnection Agreement Co-Tenancy Agreement (the Co-Tenancy Agreement), dated as of November 17, 2023, with SF 2 in its capacity as the Manager under the Co-Tenancy Agreement, for the purpose of managing such parties respective rights and obligations under the Interconnection Agreement.
M. The Co-Tenants wish to set forth herein their respective rights and obligations regarding the joint design, procurement, development, construction, installation, ownership, use, maintenance, repair, replacement of, and additions to, the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises, taking into account requirements under the Lease Agreements, the Interconnection Agreement, the IRB Financing, and the Co-Tenancy Agreement.
N. The Co-Tenants also wish to contract with the Manager for the provision of certain limited services to be performed at the pleasure of the Co-Tenants, with respect to the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises, and the Manager wishes to accept said engagement on the terms and conditions contained herein.
AGREEMENT:
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained in this Agreement and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is acknowledged, the Parties agree as follows:
1. DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION
1.1 Definitions. Unless otherwise noted, capitalized terms not defined in the body of this Agreement have the following meanings.
AAA has the meaning set forth in Section 15.1.1.
Additional Shared Assets has the meaning set forth in Section 3.6.
Additional Shared Facilities has the meaning set forth in Section 3.6.
Additional Shared Premises has the meaning set forth in Section 3.6.
Affiliate means, when used with respect to any Person, any other Person directly or indirectly controlling, controlled by, or under common control with such Person. For this definition, the terms controlling, controlled by or under common control mean the possession, directly or indirectly, of the power to direct or cause the direction of management or
3 4123-2149-0255.7policies (whether through ownership of securities or any partnership or other ownership interest, by contract or otherwise) of a Person.
After-Tax Basis means, with respect to any payment to be actually or constructively received by any Person (i) in the case such payment is compensation for Project Tax Benefits or an amount that would not have been taxable to the payee, the amount of such payment (the base payment) supplemented by a further payment (the additional payment) to that Person so that the sum of the base payment plus the additional payment, after deduction of the amount of all federal income taxes required to be paid by such Person in respect of the receipt or accrual of the base payment and the additional payment, calculating such federal income taxes using an assumed rate equal to the highest marginal rate, equals the amount required to be received and (ii) in the case such payment is compensation for an amount that would have been taxable to the payee, the base payment.
Agreement has the meaning set forth in the preamble above, as amended and modified from time to time as permitted herein.
Annual Shared Facilities Budget has the meaning set forth in Section 8.6.
Applicable Agreement means (a) with respect to SF 1, the Lease Agreement between SF 1 and Atrisco PVCo, dated as of the Effective Date, (b) with respect to SF 2, the Lease Agreement between SF 2 and Atrisco BatteryCo, dated as of the Effective Date, (c) with respect to SF 3, the Lease Agreement between SF 3 and Quail Ranch PVCo, dated as of the Effective Date, (d) with respect to SF 4, the Lease Agreement between SF 4 and Quail Ranch BatteryCo, dated as of the Effective Date, and (e) with respect to a New Co-Tenant, the Lease Agreement between such New Co-Tenant and the Applicable Project Company for such New Co-Tenant.
Applicable Battery Assets has the meaning set forth in Exhibit C.
Applicable Construction Costs has the meaning set forth in Section 4.4.
Applicable EPC Agreement means the engineering, procurement and construction agreement entered into for a Segment between the Constructing Party for such Segment and the applicable contractor.
Applicable Project means (a) with respect to SF 1, the Atrisco PV Project, (b) with respect to SF 2, the Atrisco BESS Project, (c) with respect to SF 3, the Quail Ranch PV Project, (d) with respect to SF 4, Quail Ranch BESS Project, and (e) with respect to any New Co-Tenant, any Project owned and developed by the Applicable Project Company for such New Co-Tenant.
Applicable Project Company means (a) with respect to SF 1, Atrisco PVCo, (b) with respect to SF 2, Atrisco BatteryCo, (c) with respect to SF 3, Quail Ranch PVCo, (d) with respect to SF 4, Quail Ranch BatteryCo, and (e) with respect to any New Co-Tenant, the Project Company that owns the Applicable Project for such New Co-Tenant.
Applicable Project Site means, with respect to each Co-Tenant, the Project Site on which the Applicable Project for such Co-Tenant is located.
4 4123-2149-0255.7 Atrisco BatteryCo has the meaning set forth in Recital C.

Atrisco PVCo has the meaning set forth in Recital B.
Business Day means any day other than Saturday, Sunday, or any other day when banks in New York City, New York are required or authorized to be closed.
Casualty Event means an event that causes all or a portion of the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises to be damaged, destroyed or rendered unfit or unavailable for normal use for any reason whatsoever.
City has the meaning set forth in Recital I.
Co-Tenancy Agreement has the meaning set forth in Recital L.
Co-Tenant and Co-Tenants have the respective meanings in the preamble to this Agreement.
Co-Tenants Bill of Sale has the meaning set forth in Recital I.
Co-Tenant Property has the meaning set forth in Section 8.16.1.
Code means Internal Revenue Code of 1986 (as amended from time to time).
Condemnation Event means any compulsory transfer or taking or transfer under threat of compulsory transfer or taking of all or a portion of the Shared Facilities or Shared Premises by any Governmental Authority or entity acting under power of eminent domain such that the Shared Facilities or Shared Premises are rendered unfit or unavailable for normal use.
Confidential Information means, collectively and individually, all data, materials and information (including software, data, technology, know-how, trade secrets, processes, ideas, inventions (whether patentable or not), prototypes, schematics, design plans, drawings, pricing information, customer and service provider lists, business arrangements, business information, financial information, financial results, technical information, analyses, forecasts, compilations, studies, contracts, agreements, and planning or strategy information) provided by or on behalf of a Party or the Applicable Project Company for such Party (each Party and Applicable Project Company in such capacity, a Disclosing Party) to any other Party or the Applicable Project Company for such other Party (each Party and Applicable Project Company in such capacity, a Receiving Party) or the Receiving Partys Representatives, or to which the Receiving Party or the Receiving Partys Representatives are given access by or on behalf of the Disclosing Party, whether verbally or in written or electronic form, related to the Disclosing Party, any Applicable Project Company, any Applicable Project, the Shared Facilities, the Shared Premises or the Parties in connection with this Agreement before, on, or after the Effective Date. Notwithstanding the foregoing, Confidential Information under this Agreement does not include any information that:
5 4123-2149-0255.7(a) is now publicly available, or that later becomes publicly available through no action by the Receiving Party or the Receiving Partys Representatives in violation of this Agreement; (b) is already in the possession of the Receiving Party or the Receiving Partys Representatives and is not, to the Receiving Partys knowledge, subject to a confidentiality obligation at the time of the informations disclosure under this Agreement; (c) is lawfully received from any source other than the Disclosing Party or the Disclosing Partys Representatives under circumstances not involving, to the Receiving Partys knowledge, a breach of any fiduciary or confidentiality obligation; or (d) is independently developed by or for the Receiving Party or the Receiving Partys Representatives without reference to, or the use of, any portion of the Confidential Information. Confidential Information shall also include the terms and conditions of this Agreement.
Constructing Party(ies) has the meaning set forth in Section 4.3.
Construction Costs has the meaning set forth in Section 4.3.
Default Rate means a rate per annum equal to the lesser of (a) a varying rate per annum equal to the sum of (i) the prime rate as defined and published in The Wall Street Journal, with adjustments in that varying rate to be made on the same date as any change in that rate is so published, plus (ii) two percent (2%) per annum and (b) the maximum rate permitted by Law.
Demand has the meaning set forth in Section 15.1.3.
Disclosing Party has the meaning set forth in the definition of Confidential Information.
Dispute means any controversy, claim or dispute between or among the Parties that arises out of or in connection with this Agreement or the construction, interpretation, performance, breach, termination, enforceability or validity of this Agreement, whether the same is based on rights, privileges or interests recognized by or based upon statute, contract, agreement (whether written or oral), tort, common law or other Law.
Effective Date has the meaning set forth in the preamble.
Emergency shall mean any occurrence, in the reasonable judgment of the Manager or a Co-Tenant, that (i) may arise that requires immediate action in order to prevent or mitigate serious actual or potential hazard to the safety of persons or property, or (ii) may result in material interference with the safe, economical, reliable, or environmentally sound operation of the Shared Facilities, the Shared Premises or any Applicable Project, or (iii) would or could cause a violation of any applicable Law or Governmental Approval or any directive by a Governmental Authority or operating commitment made by a Party to Transmission Provider.
Environmental Laws means all Laws, whenever enacted or in effect concerning pollution, protection of human health, safety or the environment or preservation or reclamation of natural resources (including endangered or threatened species), or relating to the use, storage, disposal, generation and transportation of Hazardous Substances or imposing liability for injury to human health, property or the environment.
Event of Default has the meaning set forth in Section 14.1.
6 4123-2149-0255.7 EWG means an exempt wholesale generator, as such term is defined in Section 1262(6) of the Public Utility Holding Company Act of 2005 and the FERCs regulations at 18 C.F.R. Pt. 366.1.
FERC means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission or its successor agency.
FERC Filing has the meaning set forth in Section 3.8.
Financing Party means, with respect to a Co-Tenant, any Person providing direct or indirect debt or equity financing, refinancing, or extending credit (including any financing lease) to such Co-Tenant or the Applicable Project Company for such Co-Tenant. For the purposes of this Agreement, with respect to a Co-Tenant, any counterparty to such Co-Tenant or the Applicable Project Company for such Co-Tenant in a swap, option collar or cap involving, or settled by reference to, one (1) or more commodities (including power and transmission) or meteorological conditions (whether financial or physical), in each case, in connection with the purchase, installation or operation of the applicable solar photovoltaic panels or Applicable Project, shall be a Financing Party hereunder.
Force Majeure means acts of God or any other casualty or occurrence, condition, event or circumstance of any kind or nature not reasonably within the affected Partys or its Applicable Project Companys control and which could not have been avoided by reasonable measures by the affected Party or its Applicable Project Company, including strikes, slow-downs or labor difficulties, fires, flood, earthquakes, explosions, natural disasters, or other hazards, acts of public enemies, riots, civil commotions, insurrection, war, or actions or failures to act by a Governmental Authority. Force Majeure expressly does not include: any delay in performing or failure of performance of any contractual provision by a Party or its Applicable Project Company (except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event); late delivery or breakage of equipment or materials (except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event); or economic hardship.
GAAP means United States generally accepted accounting principles as in effect from time to time, applied on a consistent basis.
GIF means Interconnection Customers Interconnection Facilities as defined in the Interconnection Agreement, to the extent it applies to any Applicable Project.
Governmental Approval means any permit, license, certificate, concession, approval, consent, ratification, permission, clearance, confirmation, exemption, waiver, franchise, certification, designation, rating, registration, variance, qualification, accreditation or authorization issued, granted, given or otherwise made available by or under the authority of any Governmental Authority or pursuant to any Law.
Governmental Authority means any court, tribunal, authority, agency, commission, official or other instrumentality, including regulatory authorities and bodies, of the United States or any state, county, city, school district, hospital district, or other political subdivision, any quasi- governmental regulatory authority, such as NERC, or NERCs regional reliability entities acting under delegated authority, as well as any arbitrator or any judicial or quasi-judicial tribunal of competent jurisdiction.
7 4123-2149-0255.7 Hazardous Substances means: (a) any hazardous materials, hazardous wastes, hazardous substances, toxic wastes, solid wastes, and toxic substances as those or similar terms are defined under any Environmental Laws; (b) any asbestos or asbestos containing material; (c) polychlorinated biphenyls (PCBs) or PCB containing materials or fluids; (d) radon; (e) any petroleum, petroleum hydrocarbons, petroleum products, crude oil and any fractions or derivatives thereof; and (f) any other hazardous, radioactive, toxic or noxious substance, material, pollutant, or contaminant that, whether by its nature, its use, or the consequences of exposure to it, is subject to regulation or could give rise to liability under any Environmental Laws.
Indemnified Parties has the meaning set forth in Section 11.1.
Industrial Revenue Bonds has the meaning set forth in Recital I.
Initial Manager has the meaning set forth in the preamble above.
Interconnection Agreement has the meaning set forth in Recital L.

8 4123-2149-0255.7expenses (including court costs and fees, reasonable legal counsels, accountants, or other fees and expenses) incurred in defending against or investigating any of the same.

The Co-Tenant requesting reimbursement shall provide supporting documentation to the other Co-Tenant and the independent engineer, including, at a minimum if the Applicable Project is a generating facility, for the period of disconnection, downtime, curtailment or outage, as applicable, recorded solar and meteorological data from the affected Applicable Project and a calculation of the quantity of energy that would have been produced by the Applicable Project and delivered to the interconnection point (but was not produced and delivered) using the best available data or interpolated data, including solar availability, power curves, the number of operational solar panels, station service, transmission line losses, meteorological conditions or physical limitations.

(a) Each Co-Tenant anticipates that the Applicable Projects will use a single settlement meter at the common point of interconnection with Transmission Providers transmission system (the Settlement Meter). The Co-Tenant causing such interruption, reduction or curtailment shall compensate the other Co- Tenants (on an After-Tax Basis) for the Revenue Losses as a result, except where such interruption, reduction or curtailment was in all respects required and compulsory under one or more applicable Laws. Any other interruption, reduction in deliveries, or other curtailment of electrical power through the Shared Facilities, or to the point of interconnection designated in the Interconnection Agreement, that in each case is not caused by the action or inaction of any Co- Tenant or its Applicable Project Company, and which shall include but not be limited to curtailment required by Transmission Owner, Transmission Provider, other balancing authority, or a Governmental Authority, shall be allocated as follows: first, to each Co-Tenant and its Applicable Project Company that is delivering or importing energy, as applicable, in excess of
32 4123-2149-0255.7such Co-Tenants Maximum Capacity (if any) shall reduce deliveries or imports, as applicable, down to such Co-Tenants Maximum Capacity; provided, that, if the aggregate Maximum Capacity then utilized by SF 1 and SF 2 exceeds 300 MW, SF 2 shall reduce deliveries or imports, as applicable to cause the aggregate Maximum Capacity then utilized by SF 1 and SF 2 to 300 MW before SF 1 is called upon to reduce deliveries or imports, and if the aggregate Maximum Capacity then utilized by SF 3 and SF 4 exceeds 100 MW, SF 4 shall reduce deliveries or imports, as applicable to cause the aggregate Maximum Capacity then utilized by SF 3 and SF 4 to 100 MW before SF 3 is called upon to reduce deliveries or imports; second, to each New Co-Tenant and their respective Applicable Project Companies in proportion to their respective Maximum Capacity, if any; third, to SF 2 and SF 4 and their respective Applicable Project Companies in proportion to their respective Maximum Capacity; and fourth, to the other Co-Tenants and their respective Applicable Project Companies in proportion to their respective Maximum Capacity to the extent such Co-Tenants Applicable Project Companys facilities were in operation or were scheduled to receive or deliver electrical power for the period of such interruption, reduction in deliveries, or other curtailment of electrical power through the Shared Facilities.

Within thirty (30) days after receipt of a Restoration Proposal from the Manager, each Co-Tenant shall notify the Manager and each other Co-Tenant in writing of whether it elects to participate in the rebuilding, repair, restoration or replacement of the Shared Assets. Any costs, expenses or other Liabilities associated with the rebuilding, repair, restoration or replacement of the portion of the Shared Assets affected by a Loss Event shall be Shared Expenses reimbursed by each Co-Tenant that has elected to participate in such activity, in proportion to its Percentage Interest with respect to losses associated with the Shared Premises and in proportion to its Undivided Interests with respect to losses associated with the Shared Facilities, or each applicable Segment thereof. THE STATE OF IDAHO § § KNOW ALL PERSONS BY THESE PRESENTS: COUNTY OF ADA §
This MEMORANDUM OF AMENDED AND RESTATED LEASE AGREEMENT (this Memorandum) is made and executed to be effective as of _____________, 2024 (the Effective Date), by and between Atrisco BESS SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Lessor), and Atrisco Energy Storage LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Lessee, and collectively with Lessor, the Parties, and each individually a Party).
RECITALS:
A. Lessor is a wholly owned subsidiary of Lessee, and a party to the Amended and Restated Shared Facilities Agreement (SFA), dated as of the Effective Date, with Atrisco Solar SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, Quail Ranch Solar SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company and Quail Ranch BESS SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, under which Lessor owns (i) its Percentage Interest (as defined in the SFA) in certain real property more particularly described on Exhibit A attached hereto (as amended and supplemented from time to time, the Shared Premises) and (ii) its Undivided Interest (as defined in the SFA) in certain common infrastructure facilities supporting the construction, operation and maintenance of the Project, including electrical transmission facilities, a substation, operations and maintenance facilities, laydown and staging areas for construction and other related facilities all as more particularly described in Exhibit C of the SFA (collectively the Shared Facilities). The SFA is evidenced by a Memorandum of Amended and Restated Shared Facilities Agreement dated as of the Effective Date by and among Lessor, SF 1, SF 3, and SF 4 recorded on ___________, 2024, as Document #2024__________, in the official public records for real property of Bernalillo County, New Mexico.
B. Lessee is developing an approximately 300 MWac/1200 MWh battery energy storage facility on real property located in Bernalillo County, New Mexico (the Project Site) that will include battery storage facilities and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (the Project), which requires the use of Shared Facilities and Shared Premises.
C. The Parties entered into that certain Lease Agreement (the Existing Lease), dated December 13, 2023, as evidenced by the Memorandum of Lease Agreement, dated December 13, 2023 and recorded on December 15, 2023 as Document #2023079346, pursuant to which Lessor agreed to lease to Lessee, and Lessee agreed to lease from Lessor, all of Lessors rights and obligations in and to its Undivided Interest and Percentage Interest.
Exhibit A-1 4165-5452-0401.3 D. Substantially concurrently herewith, the Parties are entering into an Amended and Restated Lease Agreement to amend, restate and supersede the Existing Lease in all respects (the Existing Lease, as so amended and restated, and as may hereinafter be further amended, modified, supplemented, restated or replaced from time to time, the Lease Agreement).
E. This Memorandum is being executed and recorded to evidence the Lease Agreement.
AGREEMENTS:
The Parties acknowledge and agree to and hereby provide constructive notice of the following matters:
1. Lease. Lessor leases to Lessee, and Lessee leases from Lessor, its Undivided Interest and Percentage Interest, subject to the terms of the SFA, the Real Estate Documents (including the Shared Premises Agreements), and the Lease Agreement; provided, however, that such lease shall be limited to the rights comprising such Undivided Interest and Percentage Interest for the development, construction, ownership, operation, and maintenance of the Project and subject to all other limitations set forth in the Lease Agreement. The Shared Premises Agreements mean certain lease, easement, or fee rights to use the Shared Premises held or being acquired by the Co-Tenants (as defined in the SFA), all of which are more particularly described on Exhibit B attached hereto.
2. Term. The term of this Memorandum shall commence on the Effective Date and continue until the expiration or termination of the SFA (the Term). This Memorandum may not be terminated earlier than the expiration of the Term for any reason, other than in connection with the exercise of any remedies under (a) that certain Pledge Agreement between Lessee and Lessee, (b) that certain Security Agreement between Lessor and Lessee, and (c) that certain Mortgage between Lessor and Lessee in each case, entered into on or about the date of financial close for the Project (collectively, the Security Documents).
3. Project and Ownership. Subject to the Security Documents, the SFA, the Real Estate Documents, and the Lease Agreement, (a) Lessee is and shall remain the exclusive owner and operator of the Project, and if Lessee transfers any interest in the Project, Lessee shall require the transferee thereof to assume Lessees rights and obligations under the Lease Agreement and (b) the Shared Facilities shall not be transferred with the fee interest or leasehold or other rights in or to the Shared Premises or the Project Site or otherwise by Lessor or Lessee, as applicable. Lessor shall not directly or indirectly cause or create any lien on or with respect to the Project or any interest therein (without limiting any obligation or liability, or any Lien, in connection with the Lease Agreement).
4. Effect of Memorandum. The purpose of this Memorandum is to give notice of the Lease Agreement and its respective terms, covenants and conditions to the same extent as if the Lease Agreement was fully set forth herein. This Memorandum shall not modify in any manner the terms, conditions or intent of the Lease Agreement and the Parties agree that this Memorandum is not intended, nor shall it be used to interpret the Lease Agreement and, in the event of any conflict between the Lease Agreement and this Memorandum, the Lease Agreement shall control.
